I am doing a EMF 2.2.1 porting from EMF 2.0.1.
The following test case used to pass in EMF 2.0.1 and is now failing with NullPointerException (full error stack appended at the end of the post.) Tested in Eclipse 3.2

public void testGetsAndSets() {
  EAnnotation annotation ;
  annotation = EcoreFactory.eINSTANCE.createEAnnotation();
  annotation.setSource("XTest");
  annotation.getDetails().put("TEST", "true");

  // Make always test pass untill fix the NullPointerException
  assertTrue(true);        
}

I can see that in EMF 2.2.1 (ecore-2.2.1.jar), getDetails method in EAnnotationImpl class has been changed as follows.


@@@EMF 2.0.1 @@@
  public EMap getDetails(){
....
      details = new EcoreEMap EcorePackage.eINSTANCE.getEStringToStringMapEntry(), EStringToStringMapEntryImpl.class, this, EcorePackage.EANNOTATION__DETAILS);
....
  }

@@@@EMF 2.2.1 @@@@
details =         new EcoreEMap(EcorePackage.Literals.ESTRING_TO_STRING_MAP_ENTRY, EStringToStringMapEntryImpl.class, this, EcorePackage.EANNOTATION__DETAILS)

In the debug I can see that in EMF 2.2.1 value of entryEClass (i.e first parameter) is null which is not the case in EMF 2.0.1. This is the reason for the nullpoint exception.

This should be a initialization issue.

As a temporary work around I have added the package initialization step at the begining and it made the test pass.

EcorePackage.eINSTANCE.eClass();

Still, I beleave EMF should handle annotation initialisation without package initialisation (EMF 2.0.1 behaviour).

